Rating: 4
This one's a keeper. Raves all around. As others have said, the ginger is essential, and making the sauce ahead is a good idea. I solved the reduction problem by flouring the scallops lightly before cooking them, which makes the sauce thicken up nicely when you add it back into the pan. It also helps the scallops brown faster so you don't overcook them. The orange juice/zest is swell, but the recipe would also work with lemon, lime, or even with grapefruit.

